  "prompt": "What universities does Bridgehampton National Bank recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Bridgehampton National Bank (BNB) may recruit from a variety of universities and seek graduates with specific majors depending on their needs and preferences. While I don't have access to the specific recruiting strategies used by BNB, financial institutions like BNB typically recruit graduates from universities with strong programs in finance, business administration, accounting, economics, and related fields.\n\nGraduates from universities such as:\n\n1. Stony Brook University\n2. Hofstra University\n3. New York University (NYU)\n4. Cornell University\n5. Adelphi University\n\nare likely to be considered, given their proximity to Bridgehampton and their reputable programs in areas relevant to banking.\n\nCommon majors that financial institutions like BNB might be looking for include:\n- Finance\n- Business Administration\n- Accounting\n- Economics\n- Mathematics\n- Data Science\n- Marketing\n- Information Technology\n\nThese majors align with the core functions of a bank, including financial management, customer relations, data analysis, accounting, and IT infrastructure.\n\nIt\u2019s best to check BNB\u2019s career website or contact their HR department directly for detailed information on their recruitment practices and preferred universities and majors.",
